    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-31T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-31T07:00:00-05:00" n="196"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">853B.111/12: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Ponta Delgada, Azores</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ponta Delgada</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-31T11:00:00-01:00"
                            >March 31, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:24 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. The local Government has ordered that all foreigners without exception
                    whatsoever residing on this island outside the city of Ponta Delgada must
                    establish their place of residence within the area of the city not later than
                    April 4 under penalty of imprisonment or deportation. The Acting Civil Governor
                    has informed me verbally that this <pb facs="0239" n="233" xml:id="pg_233"/>
                    measure applies to all those persons registered as American citizens. In the
                    island of São Miguel alone there are 94 such persons and hundreds of others born
                    in the United States who may claim citizenship. There are few citizens of other
                    nations so this order will affect primarily American citizens. The order
                    apparently was issued at the request of the military authorities due to fear of
                    fifth column activities in the event of an invasion attempt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
